         <abstract>
            <p>This companion paper to the Johnson paper points up some differences between the two authors, with this paper framing the question as: What impact does inflation have on real sustainable growth when leverage is measured in an economically meaningful way? In the presence of inflation, use of historical cost debt-to-equity ratios as measures of leverage is illogical. If managers and creditors understand inflation, they must conclude that uniform inflation has no effect on real sustainable growth.</p>
         </abstract>
